<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36204n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36204n">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36204n"> 204(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Wrestle against Holy Ghost</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[The Dukhobors.]</font> Their name, Dukhobors, is simple in origin. Like the terms of so many sects, it was used first in derision. For among the non-conformist groups were the Iconobors, who refused to believe in idols, and the Dukhobors, who, according to the judgement of the Greek Orthodox Church, <mark>wrestled against the Holy Ghost</mark>. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 112-12</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
